		<h2>Weight Forward for Better Chipping</h2>
		<p>We have all had trouble with the short game.&nbsp; It seems to come and go with the wind.&nbsp; However, this&nbsp;golf tip&nbsp;will not only help you get the ball closer to the hole (or on the green) but it can help improve your distance control.&nbsp;</p>
		<p>&ldquo;<em>Lean on it</em>,&rdquo; if you are having trouble with your short game, position your weight on the side closest to the hole.&nbsp; For right-handed golfers apply 60 to 70% of your weight on your left side (and for left-handers put your weight on your right side).&nbsp; When chipping close to the green positioning your weight on your left side with the ball position favoring the inside of your right foot (for left-handers move your weight to the right side and position the ball towards you left foot) this allows for a more&nbsp;descending blow on the golf ball popping it up in the air easily.&nbsp; You don&rsquo;t have to worry about changing your swing all you need to do is keep your weight on your left (or right) side and ball position back from the beginning to the end of the stroke.&nbsp; <span style="text-decoration: underline;">There should be minimal weight shift during the swing.&nbsp; </span></p>
		<p>So, if you&rsquo;re struggling around the greens make sure to &ldquo;Lean on it.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>
