		<h2>Maintaining Your Spine Angle</h2>
		<p>Spine Angle is illustrated below&nbsp;with&nbsp;a yellow&nbsp;line. The goal is for&nbsp;the&nbsp;golfer&nbsp;to maintain their spine angle&nbsp;as&nbsp;long as possible throughout the backswing and downswing through impact.&nbsp;In other words don't stand up straight at any time during the swing. Bend from the waste creating this angle and keep it consistent.&nbsp;A great&nbsp;drill that you can use in your next practice session is an example of exaggeration. Using a mirror make some practice swings practicing the rotation around the spine while keeping the angle the same. Use a strip of tape and place it on the mirror so you have some visual aid to show if you deviate from the desired angle.</p>
